[30;1m20 | [0m[35mpixel that is covered by the visual's geometry. At first glance, it may seem[0m

[30;1m7 | [0m[35mThe visualization[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m-----------------[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m250 | [0m[35mhe viewing volume to be in the z direction. We could design our 3D[0m
[30;1m251 | [0m[35mscene such that all objects are withing this direction but it would not be very[0m
[30;1m252 | [0m[35mconvenient. So instead, we'll use a view matrix that will map the the world[0m
[30;1m253 | [0m[35mspace to camera space. This is pretty much as if we were orienting the camera[0m
